## Security Rules

### Rule Categories

#### 1. INPUT Chain (Traffic to Firewall)
| Priority | Rule | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| 1 | `iif lo accept` | Allow localhost communication |
| 2 | `ct state established,related accept` | Allow return traffic |
| 3 | `ip protocol icmp accept` | Allow ping diagnostics |
| 4 | `log prefix ... drop` | Default deny with logging |

#### 2. FORWARD Chain (Traffic Through Firewall)

| Rule # | Rule | Purpose | Threat Mitigated |
|--------|------|---------|-----------------|
| **1** | `ct state established,related accept` | Stateful connection tracking | Performance optimization |
| **2** | `tcp dport 8443 accept` | Allow traffic to Envoy (PEP) | Public entry point |
| **3** | `ip saddr 172.20.2.7 tcp dport 27017 accept` | Allow Envoy → MongoDB | **Authorized database path** |
| **3b** | `tcp dport 27017 ... log ... drop` | BLOCK all other MongoDB access | **Data exfiltration prevention** |
| **4** | `ip saddr 172.20.2.7 tcp dport 8181 accept` | Allow Envoy → OPA | Authorized policy path |
| **4b** | `tcp dport 8181 ... log ... drop` | BLOCK other OPA access | Policy bypass prevention |
| **5** | `tcp dport 8088 accept` | Allow Splunk HEC | Log ingestion |
| **5b** | `tcp dport 8089 accept` | Allow Splunk management | SIEM administration |
| **6** | `ip protocol icmp accept` | Allow ICMP | Network diagnostics |
| **7a** | `iif eth0 oif eth1 ip saddr 172.20.2.7 ip daddr 172.20.3.5 dport 27017` | Cross-network: Envoy→MongoDB | Envoy-&gt;MongoDB bridge routing |
| **7b** | `iif eth2 oif eth0 ip saddr 172.20.4.0/24 ip daddr 172.20.2.8 dport 8088` | Cross-network: Monitoring→Splunk | Snort→Splunk log routing |
| **8** | `log prefix ... drop` | Default deny fallback | Catch-all security |

#### 3. OUTPUT Chain (Traffic from Firewall)
| Priority | Rule | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| 1 | `policy accept` | Allow all outbound traffic |

---

## Data Flow Diagram

```
                    ╔═════════════════╗
                    ║   CLIENTS_NET   ║
                    ║  172.20.5.0/24  ║
                    ╚═══════╤═════════╝
                            │
                            ▼
              ┌─────────────────────────┐
              │   zerotrust_net eth0     │
              │   172.20.2.10            │
              │  🛡️  FIREWALL            │
              │  (NFTables - Layer 1)    │
              │                          │
              │  ├─ 8443  → ACCEPT  ─────┼──→ Envoy (PEP) 172.20.2.7:8443
              │  ├─ 27017 → DROP*  ─────┼──→ ❌ Direct DB blocked
              │  ├─ 8088  → ACCEPT ─────┼──→ Splunk (SIEM) 172.20.2.8:8088
              │  ├─ 8181  → DROP** ─────┼──→ ❌ Direct OPA blocked
              │  └─ other → DROP  ──────┼──→ ❌ Everything else
              └──────┬──────────────────┘
                     │
          ┌──────────┴──────────┐
          │                     │
   eth1   ▼                     ▼   eth0
  ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────────┐
  │ backend_net  │   │  zerotrust_net   │
  │ 172.20.3.0/24│   │  172.20.2.0/24   │
  │  (internal)  │   │                  │
  │              │   │  ┌────────────┐  │
  │  MongoDB     │   │  │ Envoy(PEP) │  │
  │  172.20.3.5  │◄──┼──│172.20.2.7  │  │
  │              │   │  └────────────┘  │
  │              │   │  ┌────────────┐  │
  │              │   │  │ OPA (PDP)  │  │
  │              │   │  │172.20.2.6  │  │
  │              │   │  └────────────┘  │
  │              │   │  ┌────────────┐  │
  │              │   │  │Splunk(SIEM)│  │
  │              │   │  │172.20.2.8  │  │
  │              │   │  └────────────┘  │
  └──────────────┘   └──────────────────┘
                            │
                     eth2   ▼
                    ┌──────────────┐
                    │monitoring_net│
                    │172.20.4.0/24 │
                    │              │
                    │  Snort(IDS)  │
                    │ 172.20.2.11  │
                    │(also on eth0)│
                    └──────────────┘

* Only Envoy (172.20.2.7) can access MongoDB (172.20.3.5)
** Only Envoy (172.20.2.7) can access OPA (172.20.2.6)
```

