## Testing

### Syntax Validation
```bash
# Validate NFTables syntax locally (requires nftables installed)
nft -c -f configs/nftables/rules.nft

# Validate within Docker container
docker compose build firewall_perimeter
docker compose run --rm firewall_perimeter nft -c -f /etc/nftables/rules.nft
```

### Rule Verification
```bash
# Start the firewall service
docker compose up -d firewall_perimeter

# List all active rules
docker exec firewall_perimeter nft list ruleset

# Test specific table
docker exec firewall_perimeter nft list table inet filter

# Monitor all NFTables events
docker exec firewall_perimeter nft monitor
```

### Connectivity Tests

```bash
# Test 1: Direct MongoDB access (should FAIL - connection refused)
docker exec firewall_perimeter timeout 2 bash -c 'echo > /dev/tcp/172.20.3.5/27017' && \
  echo "❌ FAIL: MongoDB accessible directly!" || \
  echo "✅ PASS: MongoDB blocked"

# Test 2: Envoy access (should WORK)
docker exec firewall_perimeter timeout 2 bash -c 'echo > /dev/tcp/172.20.2.7/8443' && \
  echo "✅ PASS: Envoy reachable" || \
  echo "❌ FAIL: Envoy not reachable"

# Test 3: Splunk HEC access (should WORK)
docker exec firewall_perimeter timeout 2 bash -c 'echo > /dev/tcp/172.20.2.8/8088' && \
  echo "✅ PASS: Splunk HEC reachable" || \
  echo "❌ FAIL: Splunk HEC not reachable"

# Test 4: OPA access from non-Envoy (should FAIL)
docker exec firewall_perimeter timeout 2 bash -c 'echo > /dev/tcp/172.20.2.6/8181' && \
  echo "❌ FAIL: OPA accessible from firewall!" || \
  echo "✅ PASS: OPA blocked from unauthorized source"
```

### Integration Tests
```bash
# Run full firewall test suite
cd tests && poetry run pytest test_firewall.py -v

# Run specific firewall test
cd tests && poetry run pytest test_firewall.py::test_mongodb_blocked_from_external -v
```

